>> At the same time, is there any value in our praying for this?
>> Will we get karmically linked by prayer for these suffering folks?

Feeling the pain of others and being compassionate for it is a saintly 
quality. Any thought or action with which you identify strongly does become 
a karma for future. But some karmas are good and their fruits are sweet, 
while some karmas are bad and and their fruits are bitter. Thinking of good 
to someone or doing good to someone is a good karma. Thinking of your good 
and hurting someone else is a bad karma. So do not worry about karmik 
consequences when you genuinely feel compassion for someone.

